casebody.data:
Cameron William DIECKHOFF, Respondent,
v.
DIRECTOR OF REVENUE, Appellant. WD 80392 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: March 13, 2018 Scott C. Hamilton, Lexington, MO, for respondent. Morgan L. Brewington, Jefferson City, MO, for appellant. Before Division Two: Anthony Rex Gabbert, Presiding Judge, Thomas H. Newton, Judge and Gary D. Witt, Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

The Director of Revenue ("Director") appeals from a judgment from the Circuit Court of Lafayette County reinstating Cameron Dieckhoff's ("Dieckhoff") driver's license after it was revoked pursuant to section 577.041 ("Judgment"). For reasons explained more fully in a memorandum provided to the parties, we affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
